section.p:
The standard server is implemented using Servlet technology. A module
exists which implements the server using JAX-RS technology. 
This enables the usage of existing Java EE interceptors and annotations. This module does not provide the full set of features. 

The server currently supports
Conformance Statements,
@Read,
@Search,
@Create,
@Update,
@Delete and 
@Operation.

subsection.p:

Extended Operations require the correct JAX-RS (
@Path, 
@GET or 
@POST) annotations. The body of the method needs to call the 
method AbstractJaxRsResourceProvider#customOperation 
with the correct parameters. The server will then call the method with corresponding name.
